    "type": "spell",
    "data": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You steal a creature’s shadow, leaving it weakened and vulnerable. The target must attempt a Fortitude save.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The target is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.MIRkyAjyBeXivMa7]{Enfeebled} 1 for 1 round.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure </strong>The target takes [[/r 3d4 #negative]] negative damage and is Enfeebled 1 for the spell’s duration as you tear its shadow away, collecting it in your hand. On subsequent rounds, when you @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.3f5DMFu8fPiqHpRg]{Sustain the Spell}, you can throttle the shadow to deal [[/r 3d4 #negative]] negative damage to the target (basic Fortitude save). Until the spell ends, the target doesn’t cast a shadow.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the target is Enfeebled 2.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Heightened (+1) </strong>The damage when the spell is cast and when it is sustained increases by [[/r 1d4 #negative]].</p>",
